## Hypothesis Anti-Patterns To Avoid

List anti-patterns relevant to hypothesis interpretation.

| ID                       | Anti-Pattern                                                        | Why It Is Harmful                                                                      | Corrective Principle                                                                                   |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-001 | Restating dependencies as hypotheses without observable falsifiers. | It creates a checklist of claims that cannot guide tests, audits, or remediation.      | Every hypothesis must include expected observation and falsification condition.                        |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-002 | Treating implementation existence as hypothesis confirmation.       | A component or artifact may exist while the falsifiable behavior is absent.            | Require evidence that the expected observable outcome occurred.                                        |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-003 | Writing test designs instead of hypotheses.                         | The inventory becomes implementation guidance rather than falsifiable claim structure. | Specify verification mode and evidence, not test framework or commands.                                |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-004 | Omitting negative-control hypotheses.                               | False success can remain undetected.                                                   | Represent safe-failure and negative-control claims separately from positive-path behavior.             |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-005 | Hiding evidence-retention hypotheses inside functional behavior.    | Behavior may occur transiently while required evidence disappears.                     | Separate behavior production from evidence retention and linkage where needed.                         |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-006 | Marking hypotheses as true without assessment.                      | The inventory would become an unevidenced result-aggregation output.                        | Default status is `Not Tested` unless repository assessment is explicitly requested.                   |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-007 | Over-compressing hypotheses across dependencies.                    | Eval-specific falsifiers or evidence requirements can disappear.                       | Consolidate only when confirmation, falsification, evidence, and source traceability remain intact.    |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-008 | Inventing architecture from hypothesis analysis.                    | Hypotheses become design prescriptions rather than observable claims.                  | Keep hypotheses implementation-independent unless the source dependency requires a specific mechanism. |
| EVAL-HYP-ANTIPATTERN-009 | Treating policy-mediated artifacts as hypotheses.                   | It allows policy-mediated documents, judgments, inspections, labels, or checklists to replace executable checks, generated evidence, runtime metadata, validation, or result aggregation. | Model only the implementation-first basis as hypotheses; otherwise omit the source item from agent output. |

Add project-specific anti-patterns only if present in the dependency inventory.

