## Completeness Checklist

Before finalizing this hypothesis inventory, verify:

* Every dependency-inventory source was considered.
* Every included dependency source appears in the Source Inventory.
* Every included implementation-first dependency ID is represented.
* Every included functional dependency maps to at least one functional or cross-cutting hypothesis.
* Every included technical dependency maps to at least one technical or evidence hypothesis.
* Every included operational dependency maps to at least one operational hypothesis.
* Every included evidence dependency maps to at least one evidence hypothesis.
* Every included fixture, corpus, input, scenario, or dataset dependency maps to at least one fixture/input hypothesis.
* Every included generated report, report schema, machine-verifiable report data, or machine evidence package dependency maps to at least one report-data hypothesis.
* Every included negative-control or safe-failure dependency maps to at least one negative-control hypothesis.
* Every included determinism, replay, reproducibility, stability, or regression dependency maps to at least one stability hypothesis.
* Every included runtime/API public, external, capability, limitation, or disclosure metadata dependency with a deterministic execution tie maps to at least one public/external hypothesis.
* Every included machine-checkable schema validation, ontology, model-change, relationship taxonomy, identity-domain, public-contract, compatibility, validation, or admission dependency maps to at least one schema/model-change validation hypothesis.
* Every included result aggregation dependency maps to at least one result aggregation hypothesis.
* Every conditional dependency maps to conditional hypotheses.
* Every included implementation-first open dependency question is preserved or represented as an open hypothesis question.
* Every hypothesis has a confirmation condition.
* Every hypothesis has a falsification condition.
* Every hypothesis has a blocked or inconclusive condition where relevant.
* Every hypothesis has required evidence.
* Every hypothesis has a verification mode.
* Every hypothesis has source traceability.
* Every hypothesis status is `Not Tested` unless explicit assessment was requested.
* No hypothesis is merely a dependency restatement.
* Every source requirement that names a policy-mediated non-implementation artifact is reduced to independently execution-tied hypotheses or omitted from output.
* No hypothesis row, specialized section, evidence field, graph node, gate row, coverage row, status field, summary count, or open question emits a forbidden non-implementation artifact.
* No implementation-aligned machine-required artifact is omitted merely because it is an artifact.
* No exact tests, commands, implementation hooks, or architecture are invented.
* No roadmap appears.
* No actual epics appear.
* No actual milestones appear.
* No evaluation result or result-aggregation output is claimed.
* The inventory is detailed enough to drive downstream test design, verification planning, completion evaluation, and remediation planning.
